# ventilator
low-cost possibly homemade ventilator design to mitigate COVID-19 patients' breathing difficulties.

Many countries have been caught off-guard by the COVID-19, and Mexico is no exception.

Mexico, even though it is in an earlier phase of the virus compared to other countries, and right now the struggle hasn’t been the same as we’ve seen in Spain, Italy or certain parts of the United States, we are not prepared. The amount of tests for the virus is really lackluster and the gear to treat the virus is also lacking in our hospitals, especially the public hospitals, which are the only option for the majority of mexicans. 
